'----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
'Reel Output Version
'
'4 phase variable temperature Rietveld fitting of d8_01612 
'The data were recorded to optimise the synthesis of cubic ZrMo2O8 which forms by the topotactic transition sequence:
'  ZrMo2O7(OH)2.2H2O -> LT-ZrMo2O8 -> Cubic-ZrMo2O8 -> Trigonal-ZrMo2O8 -> Decomposition
'See tutorial online and file d8_01612_vt_02.inp
'https://topas.webspace.durham.ac.uk/tutorial_zrmo2o8_vt/
'
'This INP file includes output syntax for reel which lets you plot results and scan through the fits
'
'Minor modification to standard file d8_01612_vt_02.inp:
'	a. The results file name and directory name are set in section 0
'	b. The xdd section contains instructions to write the Rietveld fit to a .xyd file for Reel
'   c. It's useful to keep the same column names for Reel, with xye files it's useful to also ouput SigmaYobs as a final column
'   d. The .xyd file is appended with the calculated contribution from each phase (excluding background)
'   e. There is an instruction to run "to_Reel_v1.py" to convert the .xyd files to .xyy ready for Reel
'   f. to_Reel_v1.py will assume that the total bkg (e.g. bkg @ 0 0 0 and any peaks in TOPAS) is ycalc_total - all the output phases
'   g. to_Reel_v1.py has options for saving these background-subtracted files.
'
'You must create a folder called "results" in your working folder for the .xyd and .xyy files before running
'
'The inp file should execute the command "python .\to_Reel_v1.py .\results\" to produce .xyy files automatically
'This needs you to have to_Reel_v1.py in the same directory as the INP file
'If this fails then run the same command from a dos prompt  
'Note that the final .xyd file may not be processed in topas v7, if this happens run the to_Reel_v1.py command from a dos prompt
'
'John and Anders May 2026
'----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

'{{{ 0. Enter folder and filenames
macro dataFolderName {  } 'add folder name (with final /) if needed e.g. D:/data/topas_workshop/zrmo2o8_vt/    
macro resultsFile { results.txt }
'}}}

